                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#76ra">f. 76ra</locus>
                           <desc>-b: Donation note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"> <locus target="76ra">76ra-</locus>b: ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘተሣየጠቶ፡ በንዋያ፡ ቅድስት፡ ወህሪት፡ ወለተ፡ መድኅን፡ ወወ[ሀ]በቶ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ደንዴራ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መድኃኒተ፡ ነፍስ፡ ወሥጋ፡ ለአቡሃ፡ ወለእማ፡ ገብረ፡ ዮሐ[ን]ስ፡ ወለተ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ወለደቂቃ፡ ወለተ፡ አቢየ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወለተ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፋሐቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ በስልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           The note is written in brilliant vermillion ink and states that Walatta Madḫǝn purchased the book and donated it to the church of Mikāʾel Dändera. The note also mentions her father Gabra Yoḥannǝs, her mother Walatta Gabrǝʾel, and her daughters Walatta ʾAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ and Walatta Takla Hāymānot. The note concludes with a condemnation for those who stole the book.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title መደሃን የአለም is written on the front cover with white paint.&#xD;
- Tamallas-sign, in the shape of a cross (+) indicating the place where the omissions, written in the left margin, belong: <locus target="11va">11va</locus>.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally in the main hand: e.g., <locus target="4vb">4vb</locus>, 6va, 22va, 43ra, 48ra, 55vb.&#xD;
- Omitted letter inserted in blue pen in a secondary hand: <locus target="5rb">5rb</locus>.&#xD;
- Erasures: <locus target="20ra">20ra</locus>, 26vb, 33rb.&#xD;
- Erasure marked with thin red lines: <locus target="44rb">44rb</locus>.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections indicated by thin black lines or series of dashes above and below the word(s): e.g., <locus target="4vb">4vb</locus>, 5va, 10ra, 22rb, 32vb, 46vb, 50rb, 58vb.&#xD;
- Space for rubrication left unfilled: <locus target="48va">48va</locus>.&#xD;
- Unfilled line marked with thin red lines: <locus target="17rb">17rb</locus>.&#xD;
- Notes in pencil on <locus target="2r">2r</locus>, 76v.&#xD;
- Several names are written in the supplication formulas in a secondary hand (possibly the same as Additio 1) in brilliant vermillion ink: Gabra ʾIyasus (e.g., <locus target="7rb">7rb</locus>, 11rb, 25rb, 36va, 57va), Walatta Madḫǝn (e.g., <locus target="11rb">11rb</locus>, 19ra, 30vb, 46vb, 57va, 70va), ʾabuna Kidāna Māryām (e.g., <locus target="10vb">10vb</locus>, 22ra, 32ra, 50rb, 62vb, 70va), Walatta ʾAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ (e.g., <locus target="10vb">10vb</locus>, 22ra, 28vb, 53va, 62vb, 70va), Gabra Yoḥannǝs (<locus target="70va">70va</locus>), Walatta Gabrǝʾel (<locus target="70va">70va</locus>). The name of Tasfā Ḥǝywat is crudely written in red pencil in the supplication formulas e.g., on <locus target="7rb">7rb</locus>, 11rb, 15ra, 44va, 56va, 66ra, 76ra.</item>
                     </list>
